@spec tm_deferred_hole_spec  src=tests/specs/tm_deferred_hole_spec.lua  loc=114  sha=96c6d9e  cases=3
@exercises midiManager (h.mm), trackerManager (h.tm)
@surface   mm:notes, mm:tokenOf, mm:ccsRaw, tm:getChannel, tm:deleteEvent, tm:flush
@harness   mk{seed.notes, seed.ccs}

# Intent
  Phase D pins - design/archive/deferred-reindex.md item 1. With the reindex deferred to
  one rebuild at the outermost unwind, the whole tm:rebuild pipeline runs against
  the sparse (holed) cc array a mid-pipeline delete leaves behind. Three pipeline
  stages read mm:ccsRaw() downstream of such a delete; each must see the survivors
  past the hole, not truncate at it. Green today rests on Phase B's hole-tolerant
  iterators AND Phase D's deferral - revert either and a survivor vanishes.

# Helpers
  @fn tokenOfNote(mm, chan, pitch)  @ 10-14
  @fn ccTokenAt(mm, chan, evType, ppq)  @ 16-20
  @fn pcCol(h, chan)  @ 22-29
  @fn pasInCol(h, chan)  @ 31-40
  @fn authoredPbCol(h, chan)  @ 43-51
      -- Authored (visible) pbs projected into the pb column, as { ppq, cents }.

# Cases
  @case 'PC re-projection reads past a mid-pipeline PC-delete hole (:2362)'  [harness]  @ 56-71
  @case 'PA dispatch reads past a mid-pipeline cc-delete hole (:1598)'  [harness]  @ 75-89
  @case 'absorber snapshot reads past a mid-pipeline cc-delete hole (:2063)'  [harness]  @ 93-112

# Uses (outbound edges)
  @use call midiManager.notes  @ 11
  @use call midiManager.tokenOf  @ 12,18
  @use call midiManager.ccsRaw  @ 17
  @use call trackerManager.getChannel  @ 24,33,45
  @use call trackerManager.deleteEvent  @ 68,86,108
  @use call trackerManager.flush  @ 69,87,109
